   137	
   138	### Encode algorithm (mirror of `null_delta_encode`, `src/filter.rs:788`)
   139	Input: the window's m/z slice `mz[0..k]` and intensity slice `int[0..k]`, AFTER `nullify_zero_intensity` has set both `mz[i]` and `int[i]` to **null** wherever `is_zero_pair_mask` is true (a zero intensity whose previous OR next intensity is also zero — i.e. interior of a zero-run; flanking single zeros are kept).
   140	
   141	`mz_chunk_start = first non-null mz`, `mz_chunk_end  = last non-null mz`.
   142	
   143	`mz_chunk_values` (length == k, one element per point INCLUDING nulls, but the first element is dropped per the delta rule below):
   144	
   145	```
   146	buffer = []
   147	it = iter(mz)            # mz is the (nullified) window slice
   148	last = it.next()         # first element
   149	if last is None: buffer.append(None)     # leading null kept as a marker
   150	for item in it:          # remaining elements
   151	    if item is not None:
   152	        if last is not None:
   153	            buffer.append(item - last)   # delta
   154	            last = item
   155	        else:
   156	            buffer.append(item)          # ABSOLUTE (previous was null → store raw m/z)
   157	            last = item
   158	    else:
   159	        buffer.append(None)              # null marker
   160	        last = None
   161	return buffer            # length == len(mz) - 1  (+1 if a leading null was appended)
   162	```
   163	Key rule: **after a null, the next real value is stored ABSOLUTE (raw m/z), not as a delta.** That is why row 1+ in the dump shows `[None, 252.965..., 0.0003874..., ...]` — the `252.965` is an absolute restart, then deltas resume.
   164	
   165	`intensity` list = the (nullified) intensity slice verbatim (nullable f32 items). Its length == k.
   166	
   167	### Decode algorithm (mirror of `null_delta_decode`, `src/filter.rs:826`) — VERIFIED CORRECT
   168	```python
   169	def null_delta_decode(arr, start):   # arr = mz_chunk_values, start = mz_chunk_start
   170	    buf = []; last = start
   171	    if arr[0] is None:
   172	        if len(arr) > 1 and arr[1] is None:
   173	            buf.append(last)        # singleton peak exactly at the chunk boundary
   174	        last = None
   175	    else:
   176	        buf.append(start)           # start is the FIRST reconstructed m/z
   177	    for item in arr:
   178	        if item is not None:
   179	            if last is not None:
   180	                d = item + last; buf.append(d); last = d   # cumulative delta
   181	            else:
   182	                buf.append(item); last = item               # absolute restart
   183	        else:
   184	            buf.append(None); last = None
   185	    return buf                       # decoded m/z (length == len(intensity)), nulls aligned
   186	```
   187	Reconstructed `(mz, intensity)` = `zip(decoded_mz, intensity)`, **dropping pairs where either is null** (those are the nullified interior-zero points the reader treats as absent).
