   121	  <behavior>
   122	    Codec is null-aware in STRUCTURE (so Phase 4 ZRS can pass nulls later) but Phase 2 NEVER produces nulls.
   123	    - DeltaEncode: given a window's m/z slice (no nulls in Phase 2), returns mz_chunk_start = first m/z,
   124	      mz_chunk_end = last m/z, mz_chunk_values = consecutive deltas of length (k-1) — the start value is NOT
   125	      in mz_chunk_values (it lives in mz_chunk_start). Mirror null_delta_encode: a value after a null is stored
   126	      ABSOLUTE, a leading null is kept as a marker. With no nulls this reduces to [mz[1]-mz[0], mz[2]-mz[1],...].
   127	    - DeltaDecode: given mz_chunk_start + mz_chunk_values, reconstructs the m/z array. Mirror null_delta_decode:
   128	      start is the first reconstructed m/z; cumulative add for present deltas; absolute restart after a null;
   129	      nulls preserved aligned to intensity. Reconstructed (mz,intensity) drops pairs where either is null.
   130	    - Chunk(mz[], width): partition the sorted m/z axis into intervals each spanning <= width from the
   131	      interval's own first m/z (threshold = first_mz + width, advance by width; mirror null_chunk_every_k,
   132	      including: never emit a length-1 chunk — roll a singleton into the adjacent chunk; always emit the final
   133	      residual interval). Returns interval [start,end) index boundaries; one interval per non-empty window.
